<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17637] HttpShardHandler can wait indefinitely when retrying after certain failures</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17637</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a The LBHttp2SolrClient is used to do an asynchronous request, then any error that has a null message can result in that request not having its future completed. The HttpShardHandler loops indefinitely until all responses have been processed. So if a future is not completed, then its response will not be added to the list.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
